input: <web-search>Find current information about: document image augmentation OCR text similarity 2024</web-search>
output:
Here’s a concise 2024‑focused snapshot tying document image augmentation, OCR, and “text similarity” (change detection / comparison):

- DECDM (WACV 2024) tackles document enhancement with cycle‑consistent diffusion models to boost OCR quality without paired noisy/clean training data, emphasizing privacy‑friendly, domain‑transferable enhancement. Source: `https://openaccess.thecvf.com/content/WACV2024/html/Zhang_DECDM_Document_Enhancement_Using_Cycle-Consistent_Diffusion_Models_WACV_2024_paper.html`
- OCR2SEQ (2024, Journal of Big Data) proposes a multi‑modal generative augmentation strategy that simulates realistic OCR errors to improve seq2seq OCR models, especially for sparse character sets and specialized vocabularies. Source: `https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s40537-024-00927-4`
- Text Change Detection in Multilingual Documents (arXiv 2024) frames “text similarity” as OCR‑free change detection, using word‑level image‑to‑image comparison and multi‑scale attention to detect edits across documents. Source: `https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.04137`
- Hugging Face + Albumentations (2024) introduce TextImage augmentation for document images with operations like random swap/deletion/insertion and synthetic data generation by rendering text on random backgrounds. Source: `https://huggingface.co/blog/doc_aug_hf_alb`
- Augraphy remains a widely used augmentation pipeline for realistic print/scan/fax degradations to create OCR training data. Source: `https://github.com/sparkfish/augraphy`

If you want, I can pull full abstracts, datasets, or implementation details for any of these, or focus specifically on OCR text‑similarity metrics (e.g., CER/WER vs embedding‑based similarity) used in 2024 papers.
